latestPosts.caption:
A beautiful little seasonal number this and a firm fav of our guests this week. 

Douglas fir pannacotta, beetroot, Smokey pear, elderberry, buckwheat, noble fir, sea purslane

Texturally, this dish is very pleasant, crunchy and brittle which combines perfectly with the creamy pannacotta. Flavour wise, the earthiness of the beetroot pairs beautifully with the sharp citrus of elderberry, the floral pine and the warming smoke of the pairs. All of this rounded of with the previously mentioned creaminess and salt burst of purslane.

This dish is mega!

💚🌱🤘

latestPosts.caption:
Ciao Belli!

As promised here’s some details on our December Italian week ‘Those Posh Italians’.

From Wednesday 11th to Sunday 15th December  2024 we’re going to be banging out a very special 5 course set menu using the finest produce Roma has to offer!

Now when I say Italiano food, I’m not talking about pizza, I’m not talking about lasagna, I’m definitely not talking about tiramisu, sausage rolls? Forget about it! 

We’re going to be using the bestest best quality ingredients from the Lazio region to create a proper banging, fresh and interesting menu which shows Italian cuisine isn’t all pasta and calzone 🤪

The menu is COMPLETELY GLUTEN FREE too which is fantastico!! 

£60 per person

Book via our website 

https://www.foxglovebarmouth.co.uk/book-with-us

We’ve already had a lot of interest for this week so booking in advance is mega advised!

latestPosts.caption:
So, you know I was banging on about locally grown agretti from the lovely Ann at Einions Garden in Machynlleth. Well, this is what became of those cheeky blades of love…

Porcini, yuzu and black sesame mochi, pickled fennel, ponzu glazed shiitake, tonburi, fennel  purée, seaweed tapioca, agretti, porcini and seaweed dashi.

This one was a crowd fav over the weekend, one person even mentioned that it was better than any mochi he had whist he lived in Japan!! Now, I think he was trying to make me feel good but I’m gunna take that compliment ANY DAY of the week mate 😀💚🌱

Love you!

latestPosts.caption:
Anto and myself are continually looking for new ways to make our business more ethical and sustainable and we’ve particularly been looking for local growers to supply us with cracking, organic veggies!! Roughly a month ago Ann from Einion’s Garden slid into our DMs offering us some fantastic Machynlleth grown Agretti, of course I took her up on the offer, and over the past few weeks we’ve been getting the most stunning tomatoes, beetroot, agretti, green fig, herbs etc from Ann and John. I believe they run a veg box scheme too so if you’re up for some locally grown yummy organic veggies do get in touch with them. They are super lovely 😀

Anyway, Ann got me some beaut garlic chive flowers this week so I’ve stuck them on our courgette dish 🤪

Tempura courgette flower stuffed with vegan ricotta and fermented wild garlic, girolles, braised chicory, potato finished with girolle garum. Wild garlic capers, pickled girolles, wild watercress oil, fermented wild garlic buds, garlic chive flowers and locally grown nasturtium.

A real zinger this one with the added bonus of fending off vampires if needs be.

💚💚💚

latestPosts.caption:
Sup gang!! 

We haven’t posted in an AGE!  It’s been an absolute stonker of a month. I don’t think we’ve ever been this busy which has meant our communication has been a little bit crap lately 🤷‍♂️

Firstly, we would like to thank everyone that has visited our place recently, most of you have been absolute legends! Thanks for all the lovely reviews we’ve been receiving too, it’s very rewarding for us to hear that all our hard work is appreciated 💚

Secondly, we would like to give a brief summary of what’s going down at Foxglove in the next few weeks.

We are currently receiving a lot of bookings for next week as well as for the month of September. We strongly advise any folks that are planning to visit us to book well in advance as we tend to fill up pretty quickly. We have been turning away a lot of people recently so this is a small heads up 😀

In September we have a couple of cracking Japanese inspired events. We have our Japanese ‘Keiseki’ week running from 11th to 15th September. All deets for this week can be seen on the pinned post at the top of our page. We will also be running a Japanese fermentation workshop on Sunday 22nd September (we’ll be doing a post about this event in the next few days WATCH THIS SPACE!)

Bookings can be made via our booking page on the web 

www.foxglovebarmouth.co.uk

OH! One last thing, we have decided to open up this Sunday 25th August  as it’s bank holiday so if you fancy some veggies on Sunday eve. Get booking!!

Bought an awesome pizza kit from @pizzeriadelfina Mill Valley pop up in Marin on Saturday. We have been ordering from them every Saturday cause it’s a hit in our house! Everything comes frozen and it is delicious, quick and perfect to do any day of the week! The pizza kit comes with 3 frozen dough balls , delicious pint of pizza sauce, shredded mozzarella, fior di latte mozzarella and basil. They even come with step by step directions and the price couldn’t be better. Don’t miss this chance to get this! Go to pizzadelfina.com to find out more and to place a pre-order. Make sure to order by Wednesday for Saturday pick up. The earlier the better since they sell out quick!

latestPosts.caption:
Today we take you on a trip to Naples with this delicious “Cavatelli allo Scarpariello Napoletano” 🍅
The “scarpariello” is a tomato based sauce, and the history of this dish seems to derive from the “scarpari”, the shoemakers who, during the break from work, ate pasta seasoned with the tomato sauce and ricotta cheese , which was often and willingly offered by customers, who could not pay in cash.
Come try it!

latestIgtvVideos.caption:
70 floors on foot in a small amount of time to get up to a high-end residential building in Hong Kong before sunset. We tried to get through the security guards on the ground floor, but they knew right away who we were - we are very famous in Hong Kong. And so, as the sun was setting, we tried to think of alternative ways to get up on this roof, because we had a plan to make this extreme video. We searched every possible way up to this building, it took about an hour, and finally  we shot this video at sunset.
After climbing up to the roof we managed to stay there for no more than 4 minutes and and then the same quick descent to avoid being caught by Hong Kong law enforcement

70 этажей пешком пришлось пробежать за маленькое количество времени, чтобы успеть до захода солнца подняться на элитное жилое здание в Гонконге. Мы пыталась пройти через секьюрити на первом этаже, но они сразу поняли кто мы - в Гонконге мы очень известны. И так, пока солнце садилось, мы пытались придумать альтернативные варианты для того, чтобы подняться на эту крышу, потому что у нас был план снять это экстремальное видео. Мы искали все возможные проходы на это здание, что заняло у нас около часу и наконец на заходе солнца мы сняли это видео. 
После подъёма на крышу нам удалось пробыть там не более 4 минут и далее такой же быстрый спуск, чтобы не остаться пойманными Гонкогскими правохранительными органами.

“Let’s Play”
Series: “Other Side”
oil, acrylic and spray on canvas. 54x 65 inch

2025

The painting serves as a metaphor for human life, portrayed through the image of a woman lying
on a rooftop, orchestrating a game on a chessboard sprawling below, as if she’s commanding
skyscrapers as pieces. Her posture is playfully engaged and intrigued, yet there’s a hint of
contemplation in her gaze — the game she’s drawn into is far more complex than it seems.
The artwork invites the viewer to reflect: who are we in this game — the players, the pieces, or
mere observers? And how does every step, every decision, every choice we make shape our
destiny?

In the end, the only things that truly matter are love and the memories we create. Everything else—watches, expensive jewelry—is just glitter, temporary attributes that will lose their value over time. We can’t take them with us. All this excess won’t fill the emptiness.

But love remains. The memories of the people we laughed, cried, and dreamed with will stay with us forever. That’s what makes us truly alive.

Clyde and Bonnie

Taiwan is the most UNDERRATED destination in Asia! 🇹🇼 @taiwantourism.na 

If Taiwan isn’t on your bucket list yet, it’s time to change that. This island has EVERYTHING—breathtaking landscapes, world-class food, rich culture, and luxury experiences that won’t break the bank.

🍜 Foodie Heaven – From Michelin-starred xiao long bao to the BEST night market eats, Taiwan’s street food scene is next level.

🏯 Culture & Traditions – Walk through historic temples, sip premium Oolong tea in a mountain garden, or dress up in a Qi-Pao for the ultimate throwback moment.

🌿 Jaw-Dropping Landscapes – Cruise across Sun Moon Lake, walk the Xiao Wulai Suspension Bridge, explore hidden waterfalls, or step into the magical Anping Tree House where nature takes over history.

🏮 The Most Magical Festival – Imagine thousands of glowing lanterns all around you with wishes and dreams. The Taiwan Lantern Festival is an experience you’ll NEVER forget.

🚄 Seamless Travel – Hop on the High-Speed Rail and explore the entire country in just a few hours—because adventure shouldn’t wait.

Taiwan is SAFE, AFFORDABLE, and completely UNREAL. So why is no one talking about it?! 🤯

Tag your travel buddy and start planning your Taiwan adventure! Who’s adding this to their bucket list? 👇✨

#wavesofwonder @caneastpr #timefortaiwan #visittaiwan #underrateddestinations #bucketlisttravel

How to Country-Hop in Europe Without Flying 🚆✨

Ever taken a 2-hour train in the U.S. and still been in… the U.S.? Meanwhile, in Europe, that same ride could land you in a whole new country, with different food, culture, and vibes. No airport stress, no baggage fees—just sit back, relax, and let the train take you somewhere exciting. 

Here are some of the best train routes to maximize your travels:

🚆 Spain → Morocco (Seville → Algeciras → Tangier) | ~3.5 hrs
Train to Algeciras, then hop on a 1-hour ferry. Tapas for breakfast, mint tea by the sea for lunch.

🚄 Paris → London (Eurostar) | 2 hrs 15 min
Croissants in Paris, afternoon tea in London. Quick, easy, iconic.

🚆 Milan → Paris (TGV High-Speed) | ~7 hrs
Wake up in Italy, have dinner under the Eiffel Tower. No airport needed.

🚆 Milan → Chur (Bernina Express!) | ~4 hrs
One of the most scenic train rides in the world—think glaciers, mountains, and storybook villages.

🚆 Zurich → Milan | ~3.5 hrs
From Swiss peaks to Italian streets, this ride is pure magic.

🚄 Oslo → Stockholm | ~5 hrs
Cozy up and watch Nordic forests and lakes roll by.

🎟 Where to Book?
Get your tickets at @eurail @sncfvoyageurs (France), @trenitaliaregionale (Italy), @renfe (Spain), @eurostar (UK) or directly from the train operators.

Which route are you taking first? Comment below & save this for your next Euro trip! 🚆✨

Looking for the best date spots in NYC? Whether you’re into cozy cafes, hidden speakeasies, or romantic libraries, these five spots set the perfect mood:

✨ @conwellcoffeehall (6 Hanover St, Manhattan) 
A chic, intimate café with a touch of old-world charm. Perfect for a coffee date that turns into cocktails as the night goes on.

🛒 @thecornerstorebk (753 Nostrand Ave, Brooklyn) 
A speakeasy hidden behind what looks like a regular bodega. Step through the shelves into a sultry cocktail bar with a moody, intimate vibe.

🍸 @raineslawroom at The William (24 E 39th St, Manhattan) 
A vintage, prohibition-era lounge where you ring a buzzer for cocktails. The plush seating and dim lighting make it effortlessly romantic.

📚 @themorganlibrary (225 Madison Ave, Manhattan) 
If you love books, art, and history, this stunning library is a dreamy date spot. Wander through rare manuscripts, then grab coffee in the elegant café.

🥃 @brandylibrarynyc (25 N Moore St, Manhattan)
A sophisticated, leather-clad lounge with walls of rare spirits. If you and your date appreciate whiskey, this is the ultimate cozy, intimate setting.

Which vibe are you feeling? #NYCDateSpots #HiddenGems #romanticnyc

Best Solo Date Ideas in NYC This March! 

Spring is coming, and NYC is buzzing with events! Whether you want to explore art, sip wine, or enjoy live performances, here are 20 solo date ideas to treat yourself this March. 
Save this for later! 

	•	Macy’s Flower Show – Walk through breathtaking floral displays. 🌷
	•	St. Patrick’s Day Parade (March 17) – Experience NYC’s biggest parade! 🍀
	•	Affordable Art Fair (March 19-23) – Find unique art pieces. 🎨
	•	Spring Walk in Central Park – Enjoy cherry blossoms and fresh air. 🌳
	•	Visit the Frick Collection – Explore world-class art in a stunning setting. 🖼️
	•	See “Gypsy” on Broadway – Catch Audra McDonald in a must-see performance. 🎭
	•	NYC Flamenco Festival – Feel the passion of Spanish dance! 💃
	•	Winter Wine & Food Fest – Sip & savor delicious wines. 🍷
	•	Asia Week New York – Discover rare Asian art and antiques. 🏺
	•	New Colossus Festival (March 4-9) – Indie music lovers, this is for you! 🎶
	•	Easter Parade & Bonnet Festival – See the most creative Easter hats! 🎩
	•	Pitchfork Zine Launch (March 4) – A must for music and culture lovers. 📰
	•	GatherNYC Concert (March 2, 16, 30) – Relax with live chamber music. 🎻
	•	Women Chefs Dinner (March 1) – Celebrate female culinary stars! 🍽️
	•	Books & Burlesque (March 8) – A night of literature and performance! 📖🔥
	•	“Future is Female” at The Met (March 8) – Celebrate women’s art. 👩‍🎨
	•	Lady Gaga Album Party (March 7) – Dance to new tracks! 🎤
	•	Kevin Hart Tour (March 7-9) – Get ready to laugh! 🤣
	•	Tulip Day at Union Square – Pick free flowers! 🌷
	•	Broadway Kids’ Night (March 4) – Score free Broadway tickets for kids! 🎭

📍 Tag a friend who needs a solo date! Which one are you trying first?👇

If you’ve ever dreamed of stepping into a storybook, Alberobello is the place! This charming town in southern Italy is famous for its trulli—adorable white stone houses with cone-shaped roofs that look straight out of a fantasy movie. Wandering through its narrow streets feels like walking through a whimsical village where time slows down. Plus, the local food? Absolutely chef’s kiss 👌🏾—think handmade orecchiette pasta and the freshest burrata you’ll ever taste!

How to Get to Alberobello from NYC:

1️⃣ Fly to Bari (BRI) or Brindisi (BDS):
	•	Exciting news! Starting June 3, 2025, @neosair will offer direct flights from JFK to Bari, making it easier than ever to explore Puglia!
	•	Other options include flights with a layover in Rome or Milan via @itaairways @delta and @lufthansa 
	•	Brindisi is another option, but Bari is closer!

2️⃣ Take a train or rent a car:
	•	From Bari, you can take a 1 hour bus to Alberobello.
	•	Renting a car? Even better! The drive is only about an hour and lets you explore more of Puglia’s hidden gems.

With this new direct flight, there’s no excuse not to visit! Who’s adding Alberobello to their bucket list?

Taiwan Itinerary @taiwantourism.na 

From Taipei’s vibrant streets to the magic of the Taiwan Lantern Festival, here’s how to explore Taiwan efficiently!

Taipei – Start with breathtaking views from Taipei 101, explore the historic charm of Dadaocheng, dress up in a traditional Qi-Pao, and savor a delicious meal at Din Tai Fung.

Xiao Wulai & Taoyuan – Take a 1.5-hour drive from Taipei to Xiao Wulai for stunning waterfalls and a scenic suspension bridge. Wander through Daxi Old Street, then experience @southstreetdelight TeaHouse and explore Xia-Hai City God Temple then dinner @yangshin_vege 

Taichung & Sun Moon Lake – Hop on the high-speed rail (40 mins) from Taoyuan to Taichung and visit @nationaltaichungtheater before heading to Sun Moon Lake (1-hour drive). Enjoy a boat tour, stopping at Xuanguang Temple and Ita Thao Village and take a scenic bike ride. 

Nantou & Tainan – Begin with @hugosum.blackteagarden tea master experience and learning about black tea production. Then, take a 2-hour drive to Tainan, Taiwan’s oldest city to admire the nightlife.

Tainan – Step into history at Anping Old Fort, walk through the enchanting Shennong Street, Tainan’s famous temples, and enjoy Lunch at Fu Lou Restaurant, a highly-rated spot for authentic Taiwanese cuisine. A visit to @tendrum_tainan Culture Village, If time allows, explore Jiufen or Beitou Hot Springs for a relaxing end to the trip.

This itinerary blends culture, nature, history, and food, making the most of Taiwan’s diverse experiences. Whether it’s cycling around Sun Moon Lake, exploring Tainan’s heritage, or indulging in Michelin-rated meals, every day is packed with adventure! 

Who’s ready for a Taiwan adventure?

🇮🇹 10 Best Places to Visit in Italy 🇮🇹
Dreaming of an Italian adventure? Here are the must-visit destinations that capture the heart and soul of Italy! From historic cities to stunning coastlines, these spots have it all.

Venice – Get lost in its enchanting canals and historic architecture. Perfect for a romantic gondola ride!
Florence – Dive into Renaissance art and culture. A paradise for art lovers and history buffs.
Rome – Walk through ancient history with landmarks like the Colosseum and the Roman Forum.
Amalfi Coast – Discover colorful villages and breathtaking cliffside views. Ideal for road trips and sunsets.
Cinque Terre – Hike between vibrant villages perched above the sea with jaw-dropping views.
Tuscany – Rolling hills, scenic vineyards, and charming countryside. A dream for wine lovers.
Milan – The fashion capital blending historic architecture with modern style. Shop till you drop!
Bologna – Foodie heaven! Known for its rich pastas, vibrant markets, and medieval charm.
Lake Como – Luxurious serenity surrounded by mountains and tranquil waters. A celebrity favorite.
Portofino – Glamorous coastal escape with pastel buildings and crystal-clear waters. Perfect for relaxation.

Whether you’re craving art, history, food, or scenic beauty, Italy has something for every traveler. ✈️

✨ Which of these Italian destinations is calling your name?
Drop a comment and save this guide for your next vacation!

latestPosts.caption: Gusto Italia in Dubai offers an exceptional dining experience. For starters, the bruschetta is fresh and vibrant, while the frittura impresses with its crispy, perfectly seasoned seafood. The main courses are standout: the beef is tender and flavorful, and the salmon steak is perfectly cooked with a delicate smoky finish. For dessert, the tiramisu is a delightful classic, and the panna cotta is creamy with a touch of sweetness. Impeccable service and an inviting ambiance make this a must-visit for anyone craving authentic Italian cuisine. Highly recommended!#dubaieats #foodstagram #foodie

latestPosts.caption:
I took a trip to Chester in England and had one of the best meals I’ve had in an extremely long time. Pink Lettuce not only has an incredible ambiance in the cutest town, but the quality and flavor of their vegan cuisine impressed me so much
Their plant based menu is suitable for all people including vegans, vegetarians, and meat lovers. Cindy greeted us so kindly and had the best recommendations
They have amazing deals like when you visit 5x you get 20% off your 6th time, a 10% student discount, and weekday specials with a 2 course meal for £18.60 and a 3 course meal for £24.70
Featured:
-pastrami and Greek cheese sourdough toast
-creamy mushroom and wine soup
-calamari rings
-pink lettuce special burger
-king oyster mushroom scallops with caviar
-juicy marbles steak
-sticky toffee pudding
Anyone who knows me knows that, while im a huge foodie, it takes a lot for me to be really impressed by a restaurant. I was overly impressed with every single plate that came out. Not only was the plating absolutely stunning but each one had the most unique and perfect flavors. As a meat lover, I couldn’t tell that any of it was plant based. The creamy mushroom soup was one of the best soups Ive ever had and we were blown away by the burger. We all were so excited for the sticky toffee pudding and in my friends words “it was even better than I imagined when it came out”. Anyone who is in the UK or visiting I highly recommend supporting their amazing business and enjoying all of their delicious options!
-

latestPosts.caption:
I’ve been going to Tiki Poke in Hicksville since they opened in 2021 and they’re my absolute favorite place to go after a good workout or for a hot soup
While their poke is absolutely delicious and extremely fresh, they have more recently added on an entire section to their menu of hot food options such as ramen, gyoza, donburi, and so much more! And adding a fruit or bubble tea to any meal is a must!
They have incredible deals and combos, their best being $42 for ONE APPETIZER, TWO RAMENS, AND TWO MOCHIS! Such an incredible deal! For Valentine’s Day, if you go in and say you are following me they are extending this offer to include ANY TWO ENTREES instead of only the ramen!
They also have a great ramen combo for $22 that includes one appetizer and a ramen. And with any ramen you can add a lemonade and pork bun for only $7!
Featured:
Superfruit tea
-Amazing lemonade
-Brown sugar bubble tea
-Pork buns
-Salmon and tuna poke bowl
-Rock shrimp 
-Yuzu chicken wings
-Salmon donburi
-Spicy miso ramen
I absolutely loved everything we got, especially their pork buns and spicy miso ramen. I always love their poke bowls but it was so nice to have a hot soup on a cold night with their amazing pork chashu and ground pork
If you’re in the area head over to Tiki and make use of their amazing $42 combo deal!
-

Their menu ranges from premade desserts like macarons and cake in a jar to individually made cheesecakes and brownies on a stick. And don’t forget their hot coffee drinks and amazing milkshakes!

latestPosts.caption:
Lau Vietnamese in Bethpage is the best Vietnamese comfort food for this time of the year, especially with their huge bowls of delicious Pho!
Sophia helped make sure we got a great array of options! Not only is their food affordable but they also are huge portions so you can easily share a few different options with someone
Featured
-blood of unicorn
-Thai iced tea
-pho nam
-pineapple chicken fried rice
-beef bahn mi
-pork spring rolls 
-caramelized pork ribs
-coconut pudding
-lava cake 
We absolutely loved everything but what stood out for the night was the caramelized pork ribs and beef bahn mi. The beef was really sweet and tender and the bread was crispy but still soft. The pork ribs were tender and beautifully caramelized. As always their pho was delicious (we go all the time for it!) and the brisket was so tender. We ended off the meal with the two delicious homemade desserts. Sometimes lava cakes can be relatively solid on the inside but this one had the perfect ooze when you cut it open!
My family and I go all the time and I highly recommend stopping by!
-

I’ve been going to Burgrito’s in Bethpage for so many years and they finally just opened back up in November!
Whether you’re looking for a burger, a quesadilla, or their famous burgrito, they have it all! They also have vegetarian options as well such as their veg-rito!
Featured:
-burgrito
-burgrito quesadilla
-cajun fries
Their burgrito is stuffed to the brim with tasty burger meat, french fries, chipotle sauce, bacon, lettuce tomato, and onion. And their burgrito is quesadilla has all the same amazing fillings, with extra cheese (never too much cheese). Getting a side of Cajun fries was the perfect side as well!
And not to mention their huge burrito was only about $12 which is so reasonable! Definitely going to be a staple now that it’s opened again, head over and try it out!
-

Kashi in Bellmore had some of the most unique Asian cuisine I’ve had on the island
From their gorgeous presentations to their fresh fish to their incredible creations, everything dish was extremely impressive
They have multiple locations in RVC, Syosset, Bellmore, Huntington, and Stamford CT
Jennie and Jason at the Bellmore location gave us the best experience, helping us choose the best dishes from their new menu!
Featured:
-blood orange sparkler
-petal kiss
-crabmeat and spinach fusion
-rosemary-infused lamb rack
-tuna tartare temptation
-green tide crabmeat salad
-reef and beef
-bread pudding
We were so impressed by everything that was brought out, but especially the crabmeat and spinach fusion. It came out with such a beautiful, rustic presentation. The spread was hot, creamy, and so flavorful and paired perfectly with their soft bread. We also absolutely loved the rosemary infused lamb rack and tuna tartare. The lamb was cooked perfectly and the sauce with it was incredible. The tuna and guacamole were extremely fresh and was so good on top of the crispy nori rice crackers
These dishes were all extremely reasonable, mostly ranging from $18-$21 except for the reef and beef which was $39 but had a HUGE portion!
I can’t wait to go back and try some more of their fresh fish and creative dishes!
-

I am so excited that I got to try matcha cafe maiko in NYC! 
I’ve seen their incredible desserts and drinks all over social media lately and the experience did not disappoint!
They have two locations in NY, one in NYC and the other in flushing, and so many others across the country from California to Florida!
Their menu has everything from shaved ice to tea floats to matcha affogatos! Their flavors are so unique and fun such as their ube latte or sparkling matcha float
Featured:
-calpico and strawberry soft serve
-matcha and ube maiko special
-lavender latte float with matcha ice cream
I don’t even think there was a favorite out of everything we tried because everything was so different and delicious! The soft serve was so creamy and the combinations of flavors worked perfectly together. The slight bitterness of the matcha with the sweet ube flavor was absolutely amazing. And the corn flakes at the bottom of the maiko special were absolutely genius!
I definitely can’t wait to go back and try their menu since they have added so many amazing new options! Plus they have frozen pints for $13 which are so enticing to bring home!
-

I took a visit to Great South Bay brewery in Lindenhurst to try out their amazing food and drinks!
They have a few locations on the island now in bayshore, lindenhurst and ronkonkama! They have everything from bingo and trivia nights to live music and ladies night!
They also have a party room that still has the bank vault doors back from when the restaurant used to be a bank which is so unique!
Featured:
-Coconut martini
-Moscat love Belgium trippel ale
-Splashing pumpkin beer
-GSB Pilsner
-Sangria
-Fall margarita
-Big apple 
-Buffalo wings
-Tuna tots
-Everything but the bagel 
-Nacho mama
-Short rib grilled cheese
Favorites of the night were definitely the moscat trippel ale for the drinks, the tuna tots, and the short rib grilled cheese! The tots were such a fun fusion of crispy, sticky rice, ripe avocado, and fresh raw tuna. The short rib was so tender and had delicious gouda and crispy onions on it
Definitely will be going back and trying more of their menu and tasty drinks!
-

I had such a fun experience last week at Vida Verde in the city!
They have a super fun inside and stunning rooftop with a floral and vibrant aesthetic
The GM Trevor showed us around the restaurant and gave us recommendations for the best things to order, including the best drinks! Everyone was so friendly and the menu had so many incredible options on it!
Their taco prices range from $18-$21 for 3 tacos and they have lots of other fun options like quesadillas, enchiladas, and so much more. Plus they have a great late night and bottomless brunch menu! 
Featured:
Nachos
Queso fundido
Brisket empanadas 
Salmon birria and carnitas tacos
Mole enchiladas 
Churro sundae
Mexican candy shot
Marigold mule 
Witches cauldron
Frozen Margaritas
The marigold mule drink was the perfect thing to pair with everything we got. It was 84 oz (took the whole night to finish with friends!) and was so refreshing. Our favorite dish was probably the brisket empanadas with the cheesy inside paired with the rich brisket and the incredible buffalo aoili. The taco platter was so much fun; each taco was different since we got to build them ourselves! There were so many fun toppings and salsas to use which made each taco unique and flavorful
Absolutely can’t wait to go back to try out more on their menu, and especially their bottomless brunch!
-

I went to Chops a few months ago now for an incredible dinner and I’m so excited I finally got to go back to try out their brunch menu!
First of all JP always makes sure everybody has the best time, and our waiter Mike made sure we ordered all the best things!
Their menu is full of everything from eggs Benedict to French toast bites to avocado toast
Their portions are super generous so you can definitely get a couple things and split them! Their prices range from $17-$31 which is super reasonable considering the amount and quality of food you’re getting. Sometimes I feel like you may not get a lot of meat or seafood with brunch restaurants but these dishes 
had incredible portions of steak and were stuffed with lots of crab, shrimp, lobster, etc!
Featured:
-Toasted coconut espresso martini 
-Sangria lemonade
-Chicken and waffles
-Chops hungry king hero
-French toast bites
-Chops seafood scramble
-Steak and eggs platter (Gorgonzola crusted steak)
-Root beer float
-Apple cobbler
We absolutely couldn’t pick just one favorite but I would say top two were the steak and eggs and the king hero. The Gorgonzola crust on the steak added a sweet and salty combination, and it was cooked perfectly. The hero has the most incredibly seasoned thick cut, glazed bacon paired with fluffy eggs and pepper jack cheese
And there’s no better way to end off a good brunch with a warm apple cobbler and ice cream! We had one of those “always room for dessert” moments because of how amazing it was!
I can’t wait to head back to get another tomahawk steak, favorite steakhouse on the island!
-

For five always has the best breakfast and lunch menu and they just launched some new, incredible menu items!! I got to try a couple of their new dishes which was absolutely amazing. Along with their seasonal pumpkin iced latte; it’s pumpkin season guys!! 
Featured:
Iced pumpkin latte
Matcha chai late
Chicken Caesar sandwich
Artisanal BEC breakfast sandwich
Middle eastern breakfast
I absolutely loved their middle eastern breakfast which had incredible poached eggs paired with a refreshing couscous and delicious spices. Their scrambled eggs in the sandwich were perfect as always. They’re so light and airy and were amazing with the harissa on the flaky croissant. And you can’t go wrong with the new chicken Caesar! 
I absolutely love going to for five every single time I go. The staff are all so nice, the food is so fresh, and the portions are amazing! And don’t forget their amazing cookies and bakery section! Can’t wait to go back soon
-

Let's about the cutest way to spend a weekend! 🥹 If you haven't tried puppy yoga you're missing out! These Irish Setter pups melted our hearts and made doing yoga while pregnant much more enjoyable. I will definitely be back the next time they offer classes with shelties or rough collies! 🙊

"These are my two favourite dishes!" is exactly what you want to hear when your food arrives! ☺️💖

📍Maven 
  1006 17 Ave SW
  Calgary, AB

🥥 Kaya French Toast | $18.50 |
🇵🇭 Breakfast in Manila | $26.50 |
🍋 Hot Yuzu Mess | $11.00 | @yychotchocolatefest 

I genuinely feel like @maven_yyc never misses! I've been meaning to try their Kaya French toast for a while and it was just as good as I imagined! Kaya adds a gentle coconut sweetness and I loved the richness added from the poached egg! I was also pleasantly surprised by the breakfast in Manila. Not a dish I would normally gravitate towards because it leans quite savoury and feels more like a lunch or dinner option, but I really enjoyed it nonetheless! The garlic rice wasn't as powerful or in your face as I initially would have thought and the dipping sauce added the acidity that I needed to tie the dish together.

latestPosts.caption:
The best Italian restaurant in Huntsville opens tomorrow (3/10) 🇮🇹 🙌🏽 @osterialucahsv celebrates the bold, simple flavors of Italy with a modern twist. You will be catered to by an amazing, welcoming, warm and knowledgeable staff, who will guide you through every step of the culinary experience. The brussel sprouts were a favorite and must order. The rigatoni alla vodka is some of the best I’ve had, as it tasted as if it was imported straight from Sicily.. Delicious! 🤌🏽 also…3.5 oz meatballs in spaghetti that good should be a crime. A perfect take on an Italian classic! 
Both of the desserts were incredible as well.
Huntsville.. The hype is real. Osteria Luca should be your new Italian casual dining go-to. 

Appetizers:
Brussel Sprouts [Peanut Dukkah, Preserved Lemon, Red Onion, Ricotta Salata]

🚨 HIDDEN GEM🚨 All my Illinois people.. we judge Deep Dish and Wings on an extremely tough scale. I found a sports bar in the suburbs that knocks both out of the park. @coachscorneregv97 feels like Chicago, but in Elk Grove Village. I tried the meat lovers deep dish pizza and it was AMAZING. The sauce, buttery edges, seasoned Italian Beef/Sausage/Pepperoni/Bacon and crisp yet airy crust was indicative of a perfect deep dish. 
The Spicy BBQ wings were delicious as well. Exactly how traditional bone-in wings made to order should taste 🔥 When in the NW suburbs, @coachscorneregv97 is a must try for authentic Chicago bar foods. Sports are played on their tvs, they’re open late, and the service is excellent 🐻

latestPosts.caption:
Lure Fish Bar 🎣 was high on my list to checkout in Chicago. Taste. Presentation. Menu variety. Decor. Everything was on point. 
I recommend trying the caviar deviled eggs, if you’re a beginner fish egg eater or a first timer. They’re at a good price point here, and not too overpowering with the deviled egg mixture - a really tasty small bite. 
I love a good lobster roll and this one tasted super fresh. [Brioche, vegetable slaw, salt vinegar chips] the bun was perfectly toasted and the salt/vinegar chips were a great substitute to the traditional fry side. With the vegetable slaw, the chefs did a great job on this dish. 
The steamed red snapper was also delicious!
[Bok Choy, Roasted Peppers, Red Curry, Jasmine Rice] the quality of the fish, made it need little to no seasoning - tasted very fresh! Lure is a great mix between casual and fine dining, with Chicago and New York locations.

116 Noble is Huntsville’s premier Supper Club and location for a superior private dining experience. I highly recommend booking for any birthday dinner, family gathering, or regular cohort get-together. The space is intimate and decorated elegantly. Spicy Greens & Cornbread
Baby kale and watercress with turkey bacon crumbles, brie, honey cornbread croutons, and Dijon vinaigrette.

Southern Turf & Turf
Sweet tea brine chicken with red wine braised pot roast, pearl onions, carrots, celery, and herbs. Paired with Smoked Gouda Mac & Cheese and seasoned broccolini.

Bourbon Sweet Potato Pie

latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Looking for some of the most incredible vegan food in Atlanta!?
.
.

Then look no further than @chichiveganatl located in Edgewood! We were seriously blown away by how incredible this Mexican inspired vegan food tasted. From the tacos, to nachos and quesadilla - everything hit the spot and more!

.
.

And don’t you dare forget their famous Mangonada!

.
.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Publico Kitchen and Tap
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
You must visit @publico_atl and dine in their winter igloos before the season ends.
.
.
.

We had a majestic night dining with @publico_atl and loved our experience dining in style. The food, staff and atmosphere was top notch and we thoroughly enjoyed it. 
.
.
.

Our meal included:
1): Publico Brussels Sprouts Fried - Brussels + Nuoc cham + kimchi biz topped with fried capers

2): Pork spicy Gyoza + house ponzu

3): Calamari karaage + squid ink aioli +
 togarashi

4): Sticky Ribs with a side of mixed potatoes 

5): 8 oz ” NY STRIP" chimchuri + watercress

6): Churros and cinnamon crunch milkshake

.
.
.

We definitely recommend you visit these guys! Enjoy!

.
.

latestPosts.caption:
Classic Steakhouse Near Atlanta that’s perfect for a Date Night - @pampasatl 

Hey Foodies! This is one of our favorite Steakhouses near Atlanta that’s known for their high end Steaks, extensive Wine list and unique table side presentations. 

@pampasatl is an Argentinian influenced Steakhouse that’s become a staple in Alpharetta. Cole and I love dining at @pampasatl for a Date Night when we want a classic steakhouse experience. We recommend ordering the Seafood Tower, Wedge Salad, Lobster Mac and Cheese, Dover Sole and of course a nice, juicy steak!

The BEST way to end your meal at @pampasatl is with their Seven Layered Confetti Cake or the Dulce de Leche Crepes which are presented table side!

#atlanta #atlantaga #atlantageorgia #atlfoodie #atlantafood

Celebrating Women Owned Restaurants for Women’s History Month - @sunnysidepizzeria 

Hey Foodies! One of favorite spots for wood fired Neapolitan Pizzas in @visitsandysprings is Sunnyside Pizzeria!

This cute hidden gem is known for their unique Neapolitan Pizzas, Pastas, Gelatos and more. Our favorite dishes were the Lemon Pepper Wings, Burrata Board and the Honey Hot Char Pizza. 

Also, @sunnysidepizzeria has fun and unique cocktails like their customizable Espresso Martini! We love the fact you can add a logo, photo or design to your Espresso Martini which is so a unique addition!

What Women Owned Restaurant should we review next?!

#atlanta #atlantaga #atlantageorgia #atlfoodie #atlantafood

🚨 GIVEAWAY ALERT! 🚨 Atlanta, your next culinary obsession has arrived! @madreselvaatl is bringing the vibrant flavors of Peru and Latin America to the city, and trust me—you don’t want to miss it.

Think: Fresh Ceviches, Smoky Anticuchos, Handcrafted Cocktails, and an atmosphere that transports you straight to the heart of Latin America. 

And the best part? You and a guest could be among the first to experience it!

Win a VIP dinner for two at Madre Selva this Wednesday March 19th, featuring Peru’s most iconic flavors, handcrafted cocktails, and an unforgettable night at Atlanta’s newest must-visit dining spot.

HOW TO ENTER:
1⃣ Follow @madreselvaatl & @atlfoodiesofficial 
2⃣ Like this post 
3️⃣ Tag your foodie partner & tell us why you’d bring them!
More tags = More chances to win! 

Who’s ready to celebrate with us at the hottest new restaurant in Atlanta? 

#atlanta #atlantaga #atlantageorgia #atlfoodie #atlantafood

Celebrate National Espresso Martini Day with an Espresso Martini Tower at @yeppacoatl TODAY!

Hey Foodies! Today is one of our favorite foodie holidays of the year!

We love Espresso Martinis and @yeppacoatl has one of the BEST in Atlanta. 

Also, they have the infamous Espresso Martini Tower which comes with 12 martinis and is perfect for sharing with friends (must have a party of 6 people).

Make sure to grab your friends and celebrate National Espresso Martini day with @yeppacoatl 

Who are you celebrating National Espresso Martini Day with today?

#atlanta #atlantaga #atlantageorgia #atlfoodie #atlantafood #espressomartini

All You Can Eat Brunch at @nobuatlanta 

Hey Foodies! Have you heard the good news?! Our friends at @nobuatlanta just launched their $75 All You Can Eat Brunch every Sunday starting at 11:30AM. 

@nobuatlanta was chosen as the second @noburestaurants is to kick off this incredible brunch service and it is such an amazing deal!

For only $75 you can enjoy classic Nobu Dishes like Crispy Rice with Spicy Tuna, Lettuce Wraps with Black Cod, Fresh Sushi and more. We loved the variety of sweet and savory dishes and of course we had to get our favorite Lychee Martini in Atlanta.

Make sure to grab your reservation for the All You Can Eat Sunday Brunch at @nobuatlanta. It’s easily the best deal and best brunch in Atlanta!

#atlanta #atlantaga #atlantageorgia #atlfoodie #atlantafood

Nations Largest Wine Auction to benefit the arts at @highmuseumofart 

Hey Foodies! We found the perfect event for those of you who love wine as much as Cole and I do!

The @highmuseumofart is hosting Friday Uncorked! on March 21st at the tents at Atlantic Station with tons of wine and bites as well as live music. 

This event is just on of many events celebrating the @highmuseumofart Wine Auction which is the nations largest wine auction to benefit the arts and features several events from March 20th-22nd. 

Make sure to check the link in our bio and the @highmuseumofart to grab your tickets for this incredible event for a great cause!

#atlanta #atlantaga #atlantageorgia #thingstodoinatlanta #highmuseumofart

latestPosts.caption:
Atlanta Rooftop Restaurant with Southern Comfort Classics

Hey Foodies! This is one of our favorite rooftop restaurants in Atlanta. @thesoutherngentlemanatl is known for their unique twists in Southern Classics with locally and seasonally sourced ingredients. 

Located at @buckheadvillagedistrict in the heart of Buckhead Atlanta this rooftop restaurant has gorgeous views of the city and is perfect for this Spring weather.

@thesoutherngentlemanatl recently launched a new lunch menu with delicious dishes like the Hot Chicken Sandwich and Short Rib Grilled Cheese. 

#atlanta #atlantaga #atlantageorgia #atlfoodie #atlantafood

Fried Chicken and Champagne in Atlanta

Hey Foodies! Are you looking for a fun and unique dining experience in Atlanta? @kitchenkocktailsatl recently opened at @perimetermall and is known for the unique twist in southern classic dishes like fried chicken, lobster tail, shrimp and grits, along with creative waffles. 

@kitchenkocktailsatl is one of if not the ONLY place in Atlanta where you can get a bucket of Fried Chicken and Champagne! How fun is that!

Also, make sure to check out their weekly Happy Hour specials, Monday through Friday from 4PM - 7PM. @kitchenkocktailsatl serves a number of delicious dishes, drinks and mocktails for only $11 which is such a steal!

#atlanta #atlantaga #atlantageorgia #atlantageorgia #atlantafood

latestPosts.caption:
New Lunch Menu for Buckhead Atlanta Michelin Star Restaurant 

Hey Foodies! We were so excited to hear that the Michelin Star awarded restaurant @brushatl has introduced a phenomenal lunch menu full of sushi rolls, maki rolls and ramen. 

Known for their high quality fish, sushi and sashimi @brushatl adds a great option for lunch in Buckhead Atlanta. Our favorite dishes included the Truffle Duck Shoyu Ramen, Maki Set and A5 Wagyu Katsu Sando. 

The cocktail program at @brushatl is incredible and we love sneaking in a mid day Lychee Martini!

#atlanta #atlantaga #atlantageorgia #atlfoodie #atlantafood #buckheadatlanta

New Latin & Seafood Tapas Restaurant in Cumming

Hey Foodies! @santamaria_atl recently opened at @cummingcitycenter and is know for their unique take on Latin dishes, seafood and oyster bar. 

We loved variety of cocktails and small plates at @santamaria_atl from Ceviches to Oysters and Paella. Their Oyster Bar was absolutely stunning and they have a fantastic flair on their seafood dishes. 

Make sure to order the Seafood Tower. It’s comes with a number of ceviches, oysters, shrimp and lobster tail. Also the presentation is amazing!

#atlanta #atlantaga #atlantageorgia #atlfoodie #atlantafood

New Sushi Restaurant on the Atlanta Beltline

Hey Foodies! Did you know a stunning new Sushi spot recently open on the Atlanta Beltline

@yujiatlanta is the latest addition from @alexkinjo and is an absolutely gorgeous restaurant serving up sushi, nigiri, small plates and more!

From the moment you walk into @yujiatlanta you will be blown away be the beauty of the space and the aesthetics. We went on an incredible culinary journey of different flavors and dishes with an amazing view of the Atlanta Beltline. 

Even though it’s a Sushi restaurant, make sure to order the American Wagyu Mushroom Burger with Truffle Fries. This unique take on a burger will truly impress you, along with all of the other dishes at @yujiatlanta 

#atlanta #atlantaga #atlantageorgia #atlfoodie #atlantafood

Pasta Tower and Italian Lunch in Buckhead Atlanta- @yeppacoatl 

Hey Foodies! This is our favorite spot for an Italian lunch spot in Buckhead Atlanta. @yeppacoatl is located in @buckheadvillagedistrict and known for their Paninis, Pizzas, Pastas and incredible vibes. 

We love stopping by for lunch at @yeppacoatl and enjoying an Aperol Spritz on their outdoor patio. 

Every Wednesday you can enjoy their amazing Pasta Tower Threesome which is a staple of their lunch and dinner menu. This is your chance to choose three different pastas to create your own pasta tower and share with your friends! 

We love trying the different pasta options, sitting on their outdoor patio and enjoying a spritz at @yeppacoatl and @buckheadvillagedistrict 

#atlanta #atlantaga #atlantageorgia #atlfoodie #atlantafood #buckheadatlanta
